<org.eclipse.epf.uma:TaskDescription xmi:version="2.0" xmlns:xmi="http://www.omg.org/XMI" xmlns:org.eclipse.epf.uma="http://www.eclipse.org/epf/uma/1.0.6/uma.ecore" xmlns:epf="http://www.eclipse.org/epf" epf:version="1.5.1" xmlns:rmc="http://www.ibm.com/rmc" rmc:version="7.5.1" xmi:id="-QPFCxlAAPwRJ3PbEK2weKw" name="comunicate_test_project_status,_-LosAHFdEdy8Ac588DXPCQ" guid="-QPFCxlAAPwRJ3PbEK2weKw" changeDate="2008-01-11T11:13:03.718-0800" version="7.2.0">
  <sections xmi:id="_FU8fQHd4Edyqd9oUl_5ulw" name="Capture Status Against the Test Plan" guid="_FU8fQHd4Edyqd9oUl_5ulw">
    <sectionDescription>Based on periodic reviews of the test plans (both high-level and iteration plans), any variance to the plans are noted.&#xD;
Capture the variance to plan in reports that you can use to describe status to the development team.</sectionDescription>
  </sections>
  <sections xmi:id="_JPlI0Hd4Edyqd9oUl_5ulw" name="Communicate Testing Issues to Development Team" guid="_JPlI0Hd4Edyqd9oUl_5ulw">
    <sectionDescription>After you have identified test planning issues, discuss these issues with the development team on a regular basis. Process&#xD;
the feedback of these discussions in updates to test reports. Compile a list of major test issues, and discuss these issues&#xD;
with the test team.</sectionDescription>
  </sections>
  <sections xmi:id="_NH1MwHd4Edyqd9oUl_5ulw" name="Hold Test Effort Review Meetings with Development Team" guid="_NH1MwHd4Edyqd9oUl_5ulw">
    <sectionDescription>As the test effort progresses, hold review meetings with the development team to keep the team updated and involved in the&#xD;
test effort. If these meetings address team-generated recommendations for improving the testing, capture these&#xD;
recommendations during the meeting in a report.</sectionDescription>
  </sections>
  <sections xmi:id="_LlyLMHd4Edyqd9oUl_5ulw" name="Provide Development Team with Test Reports on a Timely Basis" guid="_LlyLMHd4Edyqd9oUl_5ulw">
    <sectionDescription>Provide the development team with test reports, test evaluation summaries, defect status reports, test coverage reports,&#xD;
and test environment reports.</sectionDescription>
  </sections>
  <purpose>&lt;p>&#xD;
    This task has two goals:&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;ul>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        Involve the testing team with the development effort&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        Convey the testing effort status on a regular basis to the development team&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
&lt;/ul></purpose>
</org.eclipse.epf.uma:TaskDescription>
